The paper deals with the problem of approximating the girth of a graph, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and has applications in various areas of computer science. The paper presents new algorithms for this problem that are subquadratic in time complexity, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) categories. The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) category. The paper uses techniques from numerical analysis and approximation algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) category. Finally, the paper involves complexity analysis and the study of algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) category.
